-- Australia's central bank locked down amid security scare
-- By Wayne Cole
-- Sun Dec 14, 2014 07:31PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Staff at the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) were safe and accounted for gunmen were reported holding hostages in a cafe near the central bank's building in the centre of Sydney.

A spokeswoman said the RBA headquarters in Martin Place was locked down with everyone safe inside. A police operation was underway in the central business district of Sydney after hostages were being held inside the cafe, where a black flag with white Arabic text could be seen in the window. [ID:nL3N0TY0SG]